<TITLE> Basanto arrives amid festivities </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com) Basanto or spring arrived officially Wednesday amid an array of bright colours and flowers. The favourite season of Bangalees is met with festivities. With the first breaking light, men, women and children gathered at the bakultala at Dhaka University Institute of Fine Arts, wearing the traditional basanti shades of yellow, to greet the season with song. The National Basanto Festival Council organised the revellers at the bakultala marking the start of Falgun, the first month of the season. The revelries were accompanied by a fair outside the institute, the centrepoint of the morning festivities. A number of cultural, fine arts and performing arts organisationsincluding Chhayanaut, Bulbul Academy of Fine Arts, Nazrul Academy, Sur Dhara, Sur Tirtha, Geetanjali, Khelaghar, National Poetry Council and Sangeet Bhabanare holding various programmes and activities in the capital. According to tradition, southern breezes should start to blow soon, marking the end of the chilly currents swooping down from the Himalayas, Basanto being the harbinger of warmth and new life. bdnews24.com
